  "text": "The increase in globalization of the business in the performance of supply chain flexibility has made it more difficult to execute business strategies. Increasing component variety, decreasing component life cycle, and demanding customers with global competition make business strategies more difficult, as these factors can motivate decision performance. On the other hand, increasing the number of facilities and decreasing the response time, uncertainty and transportation cost leads to a higher inventory and facility cost. Uncertainty is inherent in every chain element: customer demand can never be forecast exactly; travel times will never be certain; and machines and vehicles will break down [CITATION_1] .",
